From 70f5d54feead9b18849b005076a31c1e1cde257c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: User <user@example.com>
Date: Sun, 11 May 2026 15:23:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmd: add adi_hwref command for ADI PlutoSDR/M2k HW revision
 and boot mode detection

Port the Analog Devices adi_hwref command from the legacy
analogdevicesinc/u-boot-xlnx pluto branch to modern U-Boot.

The adi_hwref command reads the Zynq XADC auxiliary channel (Vp/Vn)
to sample a board-specific resistor-divider voltage. That raw ADC
value is mapped to one of 10 hardware revision indices (0-9). The
result is stored in the U-Boot environment variable fit_config as
config@<N>, which is later used by bootm to select the correct FIT
configuration (device tree + optional bitstream) for the detected
board revision.

For PlutoSDR Rev.A boards (hwref == 0) the command additionally sets
the PlutoRevA environment variable.

The command also reads the Zynq SLCR BOOT_MODE register and sets the
modeboot environment variable (qspiboot, sdboot, jtagboot, etc.) if
it is not already defined. This restores the auto-detection that was
handled by board-level init code in the legacy Xilinx U-Boot fork
but is absent from modern mainline U-Boot, which left modeboot null
and caused bootcmd to silently do nothing.

If modeboot is already set (e.g. from saved env or uEnv.txt), the
SLCR value is not applied, preserving any explicit override.

v2: the initial port used raw guesses at the PS-XADC register
protocol and got three things wrong compared to the genuine
analogdevicesinc/u-boot-xlnx (pluto branch) implementation
(cmd/version.c: do_xadc()/do_adi_hw_version(), confirmed against the
actual source):
 - never unlocked the Device Config (DevCfg/PCAP) block, which gates
   the XADC PS interface (XAdcPs_CfgInitialize() always does this)
 - never reset the XADC hard macro out of its power-on state
 - read the PS-XADC command FIFO with a single READ command; the
   pipe is one stage deep and needs a following NOP to pump the
   result out (confirmed against the mainline Linux xilinx-xadc
   driver's xadc_zynq_read_adc_reg())
 - never switched the sequencer to single-channel mode targeting
   VPVN, instead relying on whatever the default sequencer produced
 - used a different (invented) code-to-revision mapping instead of
   the genuine per-mille/nearest-100 banding algorithm
All five are corrected in this version.

Signed-off-by: User <user@example.com>
---

NOTE: The U-Boot environment must also be updated so that adi_hwref
runs *before* anything tests modeboot. Currently bootcmd and preboot
both depend on modeboot, so the simplest fix is:

    bootcmd=adi_hwref; run $modeboot

Alternatively, insert 'adi_hwref;' at the very start of preboot.
The qspiboot script already calls adi_hwref, but that call is
unreachable when modeboot is null, so it must happen earlier.

---
 cmd/Kconfig     |  11 +++
 cmd/Makefile    |   1 +
 cmd/adi_hwref.c | 404 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 416 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 cmd/adi_hwref.c

diff --git a/cmd/Kconfig b/cmd/Kconfig
